AC   P40897;
Oligopeptide transporter 1 (High affinity glutathione transporter 1).
"Sequence analysis of a 40.2 kb DNA fragment located near the left
telomere of yeast chromosome X.";
"Complete nucleotide sequence of Saccharomyces cerevisiae chromosome
X.";
"Enkephalins are transported by a novel eukaryotic peptide uptake
system.";
"Hgt1p, a high affinity glutathione transporter from the yeast
Saccharomyces cerevisiae.";
"Global analysis of protein expression in yeast.";
"A global topology map of the Saccharomyces cerevisiae membrane
proteome.";
-!- FUNCTION: High affinity transporter for glutathione. Also
    transports tetra- and pentapeptides like the opioids leucine
    enkephalin (Tyr-Gly-Gly-Phe-Leu) and methionine enkephalin (Tyr-
    Gly-Gly_Phe-Met) across the cell membrane.
-!- BIOPHYSICOCHEMICAL PROPERTIES:
    Kinetic parameters:
      KM=53.9 uM for glutathione;
      KM=310 uM for leucine enkephalin;
      Vmax=10 nmol/min/mg enzyme for glutathione;
    pH dependence:
      Optimum pH is 5.5;
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Cell membrane; multi-pass membrane protein.
-!- MISCELLANEOUS: Present with 2870 molecules/cell.
-!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the oligopeptide OPT transporter family.
